Logical_source_description.0: Electron energy-angle distributions 27 keV to 520 keV, often at 24 sec, SST Foil, Wind 3DP

TEXT.0: Wind 3dp, SST Foil energetic electron pitch angle distributions.

TEXT.1: General Notes per Lynn Wilson Jan 2015:  The solid-state telescope (SST) for Wind 3DP electrons returns a velocity distribution function containing 7 energy bins and 48 solid-angle bins.  The automated CDF routine appears to remove all the following solid-angle bins: [7,8,9,15,31,32,33] = sun/anti-sun look directions, and [20,21,22,23,44,45,46,47] = low geometry factor bins (also correspond to the SST Thick anti-coincidence detector bins).  The sun/anti-sun directions are removed to avoid X-ray and EUV contamination, which is often seen during solar flares.  The onset looks exactly like the GOES X-ray observations, which is kind of fun but not what we want to look at.  Unfortunately, these look directions can correspond to the magnetic field direction, which can limit the times when we would like to examine SEP events.

TEXT.2: General Notes per Lynn Wilson Jan 2015:   Note that SST Open (e.g., wi_sopd_3dp_00000000_v01.cdf) software removes the following additional solid-angle bins:  [0,1,24,25] = noisy.  Additionally, SST Open has 9 energy channels from ~70 keV to ~6.7 or 7.1 MeV, depending on the mode the instrument is in.  It does not appear that the routine mk_sosp_cdf.pro removes any of these ...bad... look directions, so that should be noted as well.

TEXT.3: General Notes per Lynn Wilson Jan 2015:  Inside the radiation belts, both Foil and Open saturate and suffer from penetrating particles.  The instruments are not shielded, so they can only provide relative changes when in these regions.

TEXT.4: General Notes per Lynn Wilson Jan 2015:  The data all look like they are in units of number flux or # cm-2 s-1 sr-1 eV-1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: [INTEG_T]  Integration time for the distribution

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Per Lynn Wilson Jan 2015: For Wind/3DP, this variable corresponds to the integration time for the entire distribution (it has a slightly different definition for THEMIS ESA unfortunately).  In the 3DP IDL structures, there is a tag for the start (TIME) and one for the end (END_TIME) defined as Unix times.  For 3DP, INTEG_T = END_TIME ... TIME.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Per Lynn Wilson Jan 2015: The pitch-angles can vary wildly and should probably not be displayed as the approximate values below.  I say this because there are times when the zeroth element pitch-angle can exceed 30 degrees.  This happens when the detector ...look direction... never comes close to the magnetic field direction.  It does not happen very often, but it does happen often enough to be wary of the ...approximate... values list below.
